lead_paragraph: Two men, Rupert Murdoch, the media baron, and George Joseph, an insurance executive in Los Angeles, accounted for more than 10 percent of all the money raised this year by the California Republican Party, according to reports filed today. Mr. Murdoch gave $1 million to the party and Mr. Joseph gave $500,000.
abstract: Media baron Rupert Murdoch and insurance executive George Joseph accounted for more than 10 percent of all money raised in '96 by California Republican Party; Murdoch contributed $1 million and Joseph $500,000 (S)

headline.main: 2 Provide 10% of Gifts to California G.O.P.
